<br>The Indian Institute of Astrophysics (IIA), Bangalore, is a premier national Institute in the country dedicated to research in Astronomy, Astrophysics and Allied Sciences &amp; Tecnology. The Institute has field stations at Kavalur and Kodaikanal in Tamil Nadu, Gauribidanur &amp; Hosakote in Karnataka, and Leh &amp; Hanle in J&amp;K. The Institute has embarked on a project to set up a modern large solar telescope at a suitable location in the country.
